220;Buy Now, Pay Later&#8221; in near real-time. Essentially, Affirm underw=
rites loans at the point of sale. Fraud is a massive risk to the company. A=
s <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUmOwyAQRU8TdrEYPSxY9KavY=
TGUYxQb3FBuy7dvnERqCYH0S5-HHs4gPFI-9ZYKkmsb8dxARzjKAoiQyV4gj8Fr1vJeKDkQr6Vn=
vepJKOOUAVYTFo15B7LtdgnOYEjx1aCUKzJr1TEBfBiYk1Ry3g7UgegBYPKcem7eXLP7ANGBhl_=
IZ4pAFj0jbuUmvm78u67jOJrtXCOWxqW1BmbHGSJ-kDXglA1XPk0hr_fg7_WqMH3m9ylXxn3LFR=
BfAYKbY_jZodQSCZpTzmhHe8aVUqJhDWOtZZ2wVMrOG8ot7ZwUVjImW2usvEm6PnhTdlvQuOf1L=
JJ1TGhTDvFRx8_ZrLC8BtXOWM91jwHPEaKxC_i3OHz7f6kcHxAh13_xo8HLuupkP7RC9PQtqpoV=
vWJdFUoq2afaiv_QP6KanYk" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underlin=
e;">PYMNTS highlights</a>, &#8220;Botching authentication methods could lea=
d Affirm to charge either a phantom or the wrong person, having its money v=
anish into the ether.&#8221; So the company employs a huge team of in-house=
 engineers and data scientists to fight fraud. They&#8217;re highly-paid ta=
lent playing table stakes defense instead of differentiated offense in a hi=
ghly competitive space.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Clarence&#8217;s experience is even mor=
e personal. Like Trisha, Clarence is a genius. He grew up in Singapore and =
came to the US on a government scholarship awarded to the top 50 students i=
n the country each year. He used it to study computer science and AI at Sta=
nford, then joined Shape Security as an engineer out of school (Shape was r=
ecently acquired by F5 for $1 billion). While at Shape, Clarence got bored =
and started submitting papers to security conferences on the side, for fun.=
 They were good, and conferences flew him around the world to present them.=
 His lectures caught the attention of tech publishing powerhouse O&#8217;Re=
illy Media, who asked him to write a book. He did. It&#8217;s called <em><a=
 href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUuOwyAMhk9Tdo14BliwmM1cIzLBT=
VEJVIQ0yu2HtouRLD9l_dbnGRoupZ7uWbZG3m5q5xNdxmNL2BpWsm9YpxgcG7kRSloSnAzMKEPi=
Nt0q4goxuVZ3JM_dpzhDiyV_NijlitwdpV7bGbS8GYmCghLUgwoaFBcYbvqrC3uImGd0-MJ6low=
kuXtrz-0ifi78t9txHEOpGFM6h7msvZOir1DPnr0iHj2sMN9jxmtCqDnm5Qo59LbVhknLrLbGsl=
6T6DjljGpqGFdKiYENjI2eaeGplDoA5Z7qWQovGZOjBy8vkq4LH7bdbw3mx_sCUl0uzZfalfr4c=
YcV02fQSUw9rnuO7Zwwg08YvpDal_UH27Rgxtp_ECZob8JKS2NHIQz9QukUhVFMW8tIVw6lb-V_=
0T8CYZOT" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Machine Lea=
rning and Security: Protecting Systems with Data and Algorithms</a></em>.&n=
bsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 1em 0;">Fun fact: Clarence is also in the GeekPwn Hall of Fame for=
 successfully misleading a machine learning system.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">One m=
ore fun fact: in 2019, Clarence became a lecturer at Berkeley in Applied Ma=
chine Learning.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">OK, back to that personal experience. Sha=
pe protected large customers' websites from hackers. Part of Clarence&#8217=
;s job was to take descriptions of attack patterns from security operations=
 professionals, and write rules to defend against them. One night on rotati=
on, he took in a description, wrote a rule, deployed, and closed his comput=
er. He got a frantic call four hours later letting him know that the client=
&#8217;s site had been down the entire four hours since he deployed, <stron=
g>costing them $2 million per hour</strong> in bookings! Clarence wasn&#821=
7;t fired for the error, but it did light a fire in him.&nbsp;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"=
>He realized that the disconnect between what ops people know and what they=
 can do is a cause of a lot of problems:&nbsp;</p><ol style=3D"margin: 1em =
0;"><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;=
"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
;">Things are lost in translation between ops and engineering.&nbsp;</p></l=
i><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">=
<p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"=
>There is a time lag between when the ops people see something and when eng=
ineers can implement a fix during which attackers can get in and wreak havo=
c.&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-fo=
rmat: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0;">Ops and engineering teams resent each other.</p></li><li st=
yle=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Even if=
 everything worked perfectly, there just aren&#8217;t enough engineers to s=
olve all of the challenges companies face.</p></li></ol><p style=3D"color: =
#1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Clarence l=
eft Shape in 2017. Trisha left Affirm in 2018. Both were thinking about the=
 same problem from different angles. And both joined <a href=3D"https://ema=
il.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2urCAQhJ9mWBp-BRcszua8BuGnR8koGMBrfPuL4-Ikne5Fp=
bpSn7cN5lwuvefa0L1Mu3bQCc66QmtQ0FGhmBg0Galigk8oaB6IEgrFat4FYLNx1a0cgPbDrdHb=
